Open data for the Foreign Ministry

The Foreign Ministry is committed to providing open-source data related to foreign affairs. Therefore, this webpage was created to share information with interested parties.

The Ministry provides the public and those interested with the opportunity to use this published data in studies and analyses in accordance with the open data policy. The data published on this page is legally open and can be used and reused provided that the terms of the Omani government's open-source licence are complied with.

For more information about the Open-source Data Initiative please click here.

If there is other information which you would like the Ministry to make available as Open Data, please send us an email by clicking here.

Please explain in your email what information you are seeking, the reason for your request and how you propose to use the information.
